@model MVCCapstone.Models.LocalPasswordModel


<!-- Password Change Form -->
@using (Html.BeginForm("managepasswordpost", "account", new { ReturnUrl = ViewBag.ReturnUrl }, FormMethod.Post, new { @class = "form-horizontal" }))
{
    @Html.AntiForgeryToken()
    @Html.ValidationSummary()
    
    <div class="form-group">

        @Html.LabelFor(m => m.OldPassword, new { @class = "col-sm-3 control-label" })
        <div class="col-sm-4">
            @Html.TextBoxFor(m => m.OldPassword, new {@class = "form-control" })  
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-2">
            @Html.ValidationMessageFor(m => m.OldPassword)
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="form-group">

        @Html.LabelFor(m => m.NewPassword, new { @class = "col-sm-3 control-label" })
        <div class="col-sm-4">
            @Html.TextBoxFor(m => m.NewPassword, new {@class = "form-control" })  
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-2">
            @Html.ValidationMessageFor(m => m.NewPassword)
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="form-group">

        @Html.LabelFor(m => m.ConfirmPassword, new { @class = "col-sm-3 control-label" })
        <div class="col-sm-4">
            @Html.TextBoxFor(m => m.ConfirmPassword, new {@class = "form-control" })  
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-2">
            @Html.ValidationMessageFor(m => m.ConfirmPassword)
        </div>
    </div>
        
    <div class="form-group">
        <label class="col-sm-3 control-label"></label>
        <div class="col-sm-8">
                <input class="btn btn-primary" type="submit" value="Update" style="min-width:100px;" />
        </div>
    </div>
  
    
}
